modules.description: Compares strings by treating numeric sequences as integers, ensuring "abc2" is considered less than "abc10". It includes custom implementations of sets and maps that use this comparison logic for ordered storage and lookup. This is useful for sorting version numbers, file names, or any alphanumeric data where numerical order matters.

Provides numeric comparison and manipulation operations for string-based numeric values, including ordering, min/max selection, and range checks. Works with string representations of numbers, enabling safe comparisons and clamping within specified bounds. Supports serialization to and from S-expressions and integrates with OCaml's comparison framework for sorting and ordering.
